liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A minor upset on the cards here, in what has been a close game. Jraidi's angled header was the difference. It's been an interesting contrast in styles, with Korea trying for some patient build-up before targetting their tall players in the middle, while Morocco have been playing some nice passing football when they break in attack. They need to be a bit more potent in front of goal though.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: South Korea 0 - 1 Morocco

children.content: A minor upset on the cards here, in what has been a close game.
Jraidi's angled header was the difference.

It's been an interesting contrast in styles, with Korea trying for some patient build-up before targetting their tall players in the middle, while Morocco have been playing some nice passing football when they break in attack. They need to be a bit more potent in front of goal though.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: After a blistering start, they've got the goal with a nice play. Hanane Ait El Haj sent the cross in from the right and Ibtissam Jraïdi raced to meet it at the near post, angling a header past the keeper. Historic goal, the first for Morocco at the Women's World Cup. Bernadette Clarke: "The Moroccan team celebrate right in front of their fans who are a lot louder now."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 6' GOAL Morocco!
